Let's talk a little bit about a couple more pieces of terminology

645
00:55:00,000 --> 00:55:04,000
that we'll be using extensively throughout the course.

646
00:55:04,000 --> 00:55:12,000
Okay, so remember the leading entry is the first non-zero entry in a row

647
00:55:12,000 --> 00:55:15,000
in a matrix in echelon form.

648
00:55:15,000 --> 00:55:22,000
So it turns out that the leading entries in the reduced echelon form

649
00:55:22,000 --> 00:55:29,000
and in any echelon form are in the same positions, I mean the same location in the matrix.

650
00:55:29,000 --> 00:55:32,000
So here's the one we're just looking at.

651
00:55:32,000 --> 00:55:39,000
There's a leading entry in the 1, 1 first row, first column, second row, second column, third row, third column.

652
00:55:39,000 --> 00:55:44,000
And in the reduced echelon form, same positions in the matrix.

653
00:55:44,000 --> 00:55:49,000
So it's convenient to talk about those positions as opposed to the actual value.

654
00:55:49,000 --> 00:55:55,000
The leading entry is the actual value, but we really are more interested in the position.

655
00:55:55,000 --> 00:55:57,000
And so we call that a pivot position.

656
00:55:57,000 --> 00:56:02,000
So a pivot position is a position that contains a leading entry.

657
00:56:02,000 --> 00:56:10,000
So the 1, 1, 2, 2, 3, 3 positions would be pivot positions in this matrix.

658
00:56:10,000 --> 00:56:15,000
Okay, so as I said, the leading entry is the actual value, the pivot position is the location.

659
00:56:15,000 --> 00:56:19,000
So the leading entry here is 1, it's in the first row, first column.

660
00:56:19,000 --> 00:56:21,000
So that's the pivot position.

661
00:56:21,000 --> 00:56:28,000
Here, this row, the leading entry is negative 2, it's in the second row, second column position.

662
00:56:28,000 --> 00:56:34,000
Okay, and then one other term is pivot column.

663
00:56:34,000 --> 00:56:38,000
Pivot column is a column that contains a pivot position.

664
00:56:38,000 --> 00:56:44,000
So I'll be using the terms pivot position and pivot column until probably the last day of the semester.

665
00:56:44,000 --> 00:56:50,000
So you will hear that quite a bit to make sure you understand what those are.

666
00:56:50,000 --> 00:56:52,000
Okay, two more terms.

667
00:56:52,000 --> 00:56:58,000
A basic variable is one that corresponds to a pivot column.

668
00:56:58,000 --> 00:57:03,000
And a free variable is one that corresponds to a non-pivot column.

669
00:57:03,000 --> 00:57:14,000
Okay, so for each column, except for the augmented column, there's a corresponding variable.

670
00:57:14,000 --> 00:57:21,000
So if you look and there's a pivot column, that means that variable is basic.

671
00:57:21,000 --> 00:57:26,000
If the column is not a pivot column, that means that variable is called free.

672
00:57:27,000 --> 00:57:34,000
Okay, so let's look at how all this relates to solving the system of equation.

673
00:57:34,000 --> 00:57:37,000
So I've got a tail of three matrices.

674
00:57:37,000 --> 00:57:39,000
Here's number one.

