03:36:16,000 --> 03:36:19,000
Alright, then we move over to the next entry.

2389
03:36:19,000 --> 03:36:21,000
Okay, plus here, minus.

2390
03:36:21,000 --> 03:36:27,000
This is a plus entry, so it's plus 0 times the determinant of the matrix that you get

2391
03:36:27,000 --> 03:36:31,000
when you eliminate the second row, second column.

2392
03:36:31,000 --> 03:36:38,000
Alright, then minus the next term, so minus 3 times the matrix that you get

2393
03:36:38,000 --> 03:36:42,000
if you eliminate second row, third column.

2394
03:36:42,000 --> 03:36:48,000
And then plus 0 times the determinant of the matrix that you get

2395
03:36:48,000 --> 03:36:52,000
when you eliminate the last column and the second row.

2396
03:36:52,000 --> 03:36:55,000
So that's where all these terms come from.

2397
03:36:55,000 --> 03:36:59,000
And you can see the advantage of choosing a row with a bunch of zeros

2398
03:36:59,000 --> 03:37:06,000
because the red term, the green term, and the orange term all just disappear

2399
03:37:06,000 --> 03:37:10,000
because they are all multiplied by 0.

2400
03:37:10,000 --> 03:37:17,000
The blue one though, we have to compute now a 3 by 3 determinant.

2401
03:37:17,000 --> 03:37:22,000
So we have negative 3 times the determinant of this matrix.

2402
03:37:22,000 --> 03:37:26,000
So we use the same method, choose a row or a column to expand about.

2403
03:37:26,000 --> 03:37:28,000
I chose the third row.

2404
03:37:28,000 --> 03:37:34,000
Okay, so I've got plus, minus, plus, 5's in a plus position.

