04:04:34,000 --> 04:04:41,000
Kramer's Rule is actually one of the beautiful things in mathematics, I believe.

2695
04:04:41,000 --> 04:04:46,000
It's just a neat little idea.

2696
04:04:46,000 --> 04:04:53,000
And it's a way to solve a system of equations using only determinants.

2697
04:04:53,000 --> 04:04:56,000
So it's just very interesting.

2698
04:04:56,000 --> 04:04:58,000
So here's the way it works.

2699
04:04:58,000 --> 04:05:00,000
Kramer's Rule.

2700
04:05:00,000 --> 04:05:04,000
We have A is an n by n matrix.

2701
04:05:04,000 --> 04:05:20,000
Then for any B in Rn, the unique solution x of Ax equals B is given by this formula here, which looks rather odd.

2702
04:05:20,000 --> 04:05:26,000
Notice that we've got a way to compute x of i for each i.

2703
04:05:26,000 --> 04:05:31,000
And it's just a ratio of determinants.

2704
04:05:31,000 --> 04:05:34,000
In the denominator, we've got just the determinant of A.

2705
04:05:34,000 --> 04:05:39,000
In the numerator, it's the determinant of A sub i of B.

2706
04:05:39,000 --> 04:05:47,000
So A sub i of B refers to the matrix formed by replacing the i-th column of A with B.

2707
04:05:47,000 --> 04:05:50,000
Notice, we replace the i-th column of A with B.

2708
04:05:50,000 --> 04:05:58,000
So to get x1, we replace the first column of A with B and compute that determinant and divide by the determinant of A.

2709
04:05:58,000 --> 04:06:01,000
That's the value for x1 and so forth.

2710
04:06:01,000 --> 04:06:03,000
So a neat idea.

2711
04:06:03,000 --> 04:06:07,000
So let's just use it to solve this system.

2712
04:06:07,000 --> 04:06:10,000
So we need the determinant of A.

2713
04:06:10,000 --> 04:06:14,000
That's just 8 minus 5, just 3.

2714
04:06:14,000 --> 04:06:18,000
The determinant of A sub 1 of B.

2715
04:06:18,000 --> 04:06:22,000
Notice that I've just taken B, 6, 7,

2716
04:06:22,000 --> 04:06:24,000
plopped it into the first column of A.

2717
04:06:24,000 --> 04:06:27,000
Take the determinant, we get 5.

2718
04:06:27,000 --> 04:06:30,000
Same thing, A sub 2 of B.

2719
04:06:30,000 --> 04:06:34,000
We take B and plop it in the second column of A.

2720
04:06:34,000 --> 04:06:37,000
And take that determinant, we get negative 2.

2721
04:06:37,000 --> 04:06:43,000
And so x1 is just the 5 divided by 3.

2722
04:06:43,000 --> 04:06:47,000
And x2 is the negative 2 divided by 3.

2723
04:06:47,000 --> 04:06:51,000
And those are the values of x1 and x2.

