06:33:22,240 --> 06:33:28,320
is the number of vectors in this basis, which is 3.

4634
06:33:28,320 --> 06:33:32,280
To get a basis for the column space of B, we look at B.

4635
06:33:32,280 --> 06:33:38,000
It's already an echelon form, so we choose the pivot columns,

4636
06:33:38,000 --> 06:33:41,480
and so we get the first, second, and fourth columns.

4637
06:33:41,480 --> 06:33:44,480
That's the basis for the column space of B.

4638
06:33:44,480 --> 06:33:47,080
And the dimension of the column space of B

4639
06:33:47,080 --> 06:33:48,760
counts the vectors in a basis.

4640
06:33:48,760 --> 06:33:50,120
That's 3.

4641
06:33:50,120 --> 06:33:55,680
So the dimension of the column space of B is 3.

4642
06:33:55,680 --> 06:33:58,720
All right, what about a basis for the row space of A,

4643
06:33:58,720 --> 06:34:00,040
in which we know from the theorem

4644
06:34:00,040 --> 06:34:03,000
will also be a basis for the row space of B?

4645
06:34:03,000 --> 06:34:05,520
Well, according to the theorem, put A in echelon form

4646
06:34:05,520 --> 06:34:07,840
and choose the non-zero rows.

4647
06:34:07,840 --> 06:34:11,640
So we do that, we get the first, second, and third rows of B,

4648
06:34:11,640 --> 06:34:14,840
which are given here.

4649
06:34:14,840 --> 06:34:17,760
So the dimension of the row space of A

4650
06:34:17,760 --> 06:34:19,880
is equal to the dimension of the row space of B,

4651
06:34:19,880 --> 06:34:23,000
and notice there's three vectors here, so that is 3.

4652
06:34:26,680 --> 06:34:29,680
All right, so we got the dimension of the column space of A

4653
06:34:29,680 --> 06:34:33,680
is 3, dimension of the row space of A is 3,

4654
06:34:33,680 --> 06:34:36,680
and the question is, is this a coincidence

