All right, back to this one.

4679
06:35:59,680 --> 06:36:01,680
Let's talk about the null space.

4680
06:36:01,680 --> 06:36:04,680
What is the dimension of the null space of A?

4681
06:36:04,680 --> 06:36:10,680
Well, we end up with a...

4682
06:36:10,680 --> 06:36:14,680
We want to find a basis for the null space, right?

4683
06:36:14,680 --> 06:36:17,680
We solve AX equals zero

4684
06:36:17,680 --> 06:36:20,680
and write our solution in parametric vector form,

4685
06:36:20,680 --> 06:36:24,680
and those vectors will be a basis for the null space of A.

4686
06:36:24,680 --> 06:36:28,680
Now, how many vectors do you end up with in that case?

4687
06:36:28,680 --> 06:36:31,680
Well, you end up with one for each free variable.

4688
06:36:31,680 --> 06:36:35,680
Okay, the key is one for each free variable.

4689
06:36:35,680 --> 06:36:38,680
And if you think about that a little more,

4690
06:36:38,680 --> 06:36:42,680
you think, hmm, well, where do I get a free variable?

4691
06:36:42,680 --> 06:36:45,680
Well, a free variable is one whose column

4692
06:36:45,680 --> 06:36:47,680
does not contain a pivot position.

4693
06:36:47,680 --> 06:36:49,680
So the dimension of the null space

4694
06:36:49,680 --> 06:36:53,680
is a number of free variables in AX equals zero,

4695
06:36:53,680 --> 06:36:59,680
also equal to the number of non-pivot columns in the matrix.

4696
06:36:59,680 --> 06:37:02,680
Okay, for this particular matrix,

4697
06:37:02,680 --> 06:37:04,680
dimension of the null space is three,

4698
06:37:04,680 --> 06:37:06,680
because here's a non-pivot column,

4699
06:37:06,680 --> 06:37:09,680
the third one, and the fourth and...

4700
06:37:09,680 --> 06:37:10,680
Oh, fifth and sixth.

4701
06:37:10,680 --> 06:37:13,680
So the third column, fifth column, sixth column,

4702
06:37:13,680 --> 06:37:15,680
is called non-pivot columns,

4703
06:37:15,680 --> 06:37:18,680
so we have three non-pivot columns,

4704
06:37:18,680 --> 06:37:23,680
and therefore the dimension of the null space is three.

4705
06:37:23,680 --> 06:37:27,680
All right, so once again, this number three pops up.

4706
06:37:27,680 --> 06:37:29,680
We have dimension of the column space is three,

4707
06:37:29,680 --> 06:37:31,680
dimension of the null space is three.

4708
06:37:31,680 --> 06:37:35,680
So I ask again, is this a coincidence?

4709
06:37:35,680 --> 06:37:41,680
Hmm, and the answer is...

4710
06:37:41,680 --> 06:37:43,680
It is a coincidence.

4711
06:37:43,680 --> 06:37:47,680
It's a coincidence because dimension of the column space

4712
06:37:47,680 --> 06:37:49,680
is the number of pivot columns,

4713
06:37:49,680 --> 06:37:53,680
dimension of the null space is the number of non-pivot columns.

4714
06:37:53,680 --> 06:37:56,680
So when you add them together, you get what?

4715
06:37:56,680 --> 06:37:58,680
The number of columns in the matrix.

4716
06:37:58,680 --> 06:38:01,680
So it just so happened that there were six columns

4717
06:38:01,680 --> 06:38:04,680
in this matrix, and so if the dimension of the column space

4718
06:38:04,680 --> 06:38:07,680
is three, then the dimension of the null space

4719
06:38:07,680 --> 06:38:10,680
is going to be six minus three, which is also three.

4720
06:38:10,680 --> 06:38:12,680
That's totally coincidence.

4721
06:38:12,680 --> 06:38:16,680
Had there been seven columns, the dimension of the null space

4722
06:38:16,680 --> 06:38:18,680
would have been four.

4723
06:38:18,680 --> 06:38:21,680
All right, so we have the dimension of the column space

4724
06:38:21,680 --> 06:38:23,680
plus the dimension of the null space is equal

4725
06:38:23,680 --> 06:38:25,680
to the number of columns,

4726
06:38:25,680 --> 06:38:27,680
and since the dimension of the column space

4727
06:38:27,680 --> 06:38:29,680
is equal to the dimension of the row space,

4728
06:38:29,680 --> 06:38:31,680
we have the dimension of the row space

4729
06:38:31,680 --> 06:38:33,680
plus the dimension of the null space

4730
06:38:33,680 --> 06:38:36,680
is equal to the number of columns,

4731
06:38:36,680 --> 06:38:44,380
one more time since the dimension of the column space and the dimension of the row space are equal to the rank of a.

4732
06:38:44,380 --> 06:38:52,460
We have the rank plus the dimension of the null space is equal to the number of columns.

4733
06:38:52,460 --> 06:38:59,260
