06:41:08,460 --> 06:41:14,760
That falls from number three since the dimension of the column space is equal to the rank of a matrix.

4760
06:41:14,760 --> 06:41:18,560
Okay, then we have two more that deal with the null space.

4761
06:41:18,560 --> 06:41:22,760
Null space of A is just the zero vector.

4762
06:41:22,760 --> 06:41:31,460
Okay, so if that's true, then that means that if we look at the system AX equals zero, it has only the trivial solution.

4763
06:41:31,460 --> 06:41:41,460
That happens when there are no free variables, which means there's a pivot position in every column, which means they're in pivot positions.

4764
06:41:41,460 --> 06:41:51,060
And from number five follows number six because if you have only the zero vector, then that's a special case.

4765
06:41:51,060 --> 06:41:57,560
And we define the dimension of that vector space to be zero.

4766
06:41:57,560 --> 06:42:02,760
All right, so all these are equivalent to the statement that A is an invertible matrix.

4767
06:42:02,760 --> 06:42:09,760
So just like with those, the first ten, I believe it was, let's see, yep, first ten.

