06:43:42,960 --> 06:43:48,160
If the null space of a seven by six matrix is five dimensional.

4785
06:43:48,160 --> 06:44:02,660
Okay, so that means you have five non-pivot columns, which means out of six columns, one is a pivot column, then therefore the dimension of the column space has to be one.

4786
06:44:02,660 --> 06:44:10,260
All right, suppose the null space of a five by six matrix is four dimensional.

4787
06:44:10,260 --> 06:44:20,360
Then that means you have four non-pivot columns, so that leaves two pivot columns and we want to know the dimension of the row space.

4788
06:44:20,360 --> 06:44:26,760
We have two pivot columns, so that means we have two non-zero rows when we put the matrix in echelon form.

4789
06:44:26,760 --> 06:44:30,860
