06:47:30,060 --> 06:47:33,760
And that is because you have a pivot position in every row.

4818
06:47:33,760 --> 06:47:40,360
So you're never going to end up with a row of all zeros and then something not zero over here.

4819
06:47:40,360 --> 06:47:41,660
All right, another one.

4820
06:47:41,660 --> 06:47:54,160
Is it possible that all solutions of a homogeneous system of two equations and four unknowns are multiples of one fixed nonzero solution?

4821
06:47:54,160 --> 06:47:59,660
Okay, homogeneous system, two equations and four unknowns.

4822
06:47:59,660 --> 06:48:06,760
So if you think about that, we've got two rows and four columns, so we have at least two free variables.

4823
06:48:06,760 --> 06:48:13,860
So if we wrote our solution in parametric vector form, so we had two free variables, then it would look like this.

4824
06:48:13,860 --> 06:48:23,160
You know, what this says is that each solution is a linear combination of two fixed nonzero solutions, right?

4825
06:48:23,160 --> 06:48:29,060
Each one of these vectors is what they're calling a fixed nonzero solution.

4826
06:48:29,060 --> 06:48:32,360
So we're going to have at least two of these vectors.

