06:50:17,260 --> 06:50:25,260
And to get us going on that, look at a small example.

4844
06:50:25,260 --> 06:50:36,160
So let's suppose in a given urban area, each year, 5% of the population that's in the city moves to the suburbs

4845
06:50:36,160 --> 06:50:40,860
and 3% of the suburban population moves to the city.

4846
06:50:40,860 --> 06:50:46,160
And we're going to assume that this is a closed system here.

4847
06:50:46,160 --> 06:50:52,560
So any movement just goes from the city to the suburbs or suburbs to the city.

4848
06:50:52,560 --> 06:50:58,260
So we're not considering moving elsewhere or people moving in from elsewhere.

4849
06:50:58,260 --> 06:51:03,460
So just city to suburban, suburban to city.

4850
06:51:03,460 --> 06:51:07,860
Okay, so let's assume that the current city population is 600,000

4851
06:51:07,860 --> 06:51:11,560
and the current suburban population is 400,000.

4852
06:51:11,560 --> 06:51:17,460
Then what will the population of each be a year from now?

4853
06:51:17,460 --> 06:51:27,160
Well, based on what we know next year, the city population is going to be 95% of what it is now, right?

4854
06:51:27,160 --> 06:51:32,060
Because we each year 5% leave, so we're keeping 95%.

4855
06:51:32,060 --> 06:51:41,760
And then 3% of the suburban population moves to the city, so we add on 0.03 times the current suburban population.

4856
06:51:41,760 --> 06:51:49,660
So that's 0.95 times 600,000 plus 0.03 times 400,000, which gives us 582,000.

